Further information
Provide Guidance and Clarification to the internal team for Quality system regulatory requirements . Responsible for product registrations in the various markets .
Working closely with QA for site QSR / CE IVD compliance , and Applied markets and Animal Health compliance.
Prepare product regulatory submissions in the region and support submissions in other regions
Monitor the regulatory development and trends in the region and report impact to the organization
Regulatory education and dissemination to the organization
Build rapport with regulatory agencies and notified bodies as required , to perform effective and fast approvals for product registrations
Ensure the business compliance with regional / global regulations / requirements ; such as FDA , HSA , CE IVD .
Review labeling and promotional materials for regulatory complianceMinimum Qualifications (must have)Degree in Science / Lifescience or Engineering Knowledge and experience in regulatory requirements : FDA 21cfr part 820 , EU CE IVDD , ISO 9001 / 13485Experience in product regulatory submissions / registrations 3 to 5 years experiences in medical device or IVD industry*LI-NG1 Preferred Qualifications (nice to have)NAEOE
